<br>
&quot;I'll put a real cast on if we can make it back to my hideout. Now, where are these weapons?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taylea>Taylea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#8B4513>(7/16/03 1:58 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://rose-needles.net/tayav.jpg width=134 height=190></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Back to Vania's</span><hr size=1> Taylee shook her head as she watched George decimate one of Vania's chairs to splint his leg. Dropping the bundle of clothes she'd been carrying all this time, she sat down on the bed. If he didn't want help she sure as hell wasn't going to argue with him.<br>
<br>
She hadn't realized how tired she was until now. It had been a long night, what with outrunning Cale's friends then coming down here with Vania. Turning slightly, Taylee looked longingly back at the bed, hoping that she'd be able to get some rest before the others planned on going back out.<br>
<br>
Hearing George say <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;I'll put a real cast on if we can make it back to my hideout. Now, where are these weapons?&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Taylee let out a small sigh. there was no way she trusted this man enough to go to his 'hideout'. Hell, there was no way she trusted him, period. Looking at him, she spoke up for the first time since entering the room, &quot; I don't know about you....&quot; she glanced at Cynthia, including her, &quot;but I think we should rest before we go out there.&quot; Shrugging, she continued, &quot;or...you can leave me here, and come back after you get your weapons. I guess the choice is yours.&quot;<br>
<br>
Not waiting for their answer she slid the worn leather coat off, tossing it to the foot of the bed, then plopped down on the bed and stretched out. 'Damn,' she thought, a real smile creeping across her features, 'it's been a long time since I've slept in a real bed.'<br>
<br>
